cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.SD

The paper discusses the use of stochastic configuration networks (SCNs) for image data analytics, which is a topic that falls under the computer science sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and sound (cs.SD). Given that the paper focuses on the extension of SCNs to two-dimensional versions for image data modelling, it is most likely to belong to cs.LG and cs.CV. However, since the paper also presents theoretical analyses on the goodness of 2DSCNs against SCNs, it could also be relevant to cs.NE and cs.AI. Finally, since the paper deals with image data, it could also be relevant to cs.SD.
